The paper deals with semantic video segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper proposes a neural architecture search solution, which involves predicting the choice of operations and their sequential arrangement, making it likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common theme in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper deals with video datasets, which is a common theme in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks for video segmentation, which can be applied in robotics, making it likely to belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category.
